0.Name: Phase On
0.Description: Set when NEMA Phase On becomes active, either upon start of green or walk interval, whichever occurs first.

1.Name: Phase Begin Green
1.Description: Set when either solid or flashing green indication has begun.

2.Name: Phase Check
2.Description: Set when a conflicting call is registered against the active phase.

3.Name: Phase Min Complete
3.Description: Set when phase min timer expires.

4.Name: Phase Gap Out
4.Description: Phase termination due to gap out termination condition. Set once per phase when phase gaps out but may not necessarily occur upon phase termination.

5.Name: Phase Max Out
5.Description: Set when phase max timer expires, but may not necessarily occur upon phase termination.

6.Name: Phase Forceoff
6.Description: Set when phase forceoff is applied by the coordinator to the active green phase.

7.Name: Phase Green Termination
7.Description: Set when phase green indications are terminated into either yellow change interval or permissive (FYA) movement.

8.Name: Phase Begin Yellow Clearance
8.Description: Set when phase yellow indication becomes active and interval timer begins.

9.Name: Phase End Yellow Clearance
9.Description: Set when phase yellow indication become inactive.

10.Name: Phase Begin Red Clearance
10.Description: Set only if phase red clearance is served.  Set when red clearance timing begins.

11.Name: Phase End Red Clearance
11.Description: Set only if phase red clearance is served.  Set when red clearance timing concludes.

12.Name: Phase Inactive
12.Description: Set when the phase is no longer active within the ring, including completion of any trailing overlaps or end of barrier delays.

13.Name: Extension Timer Gap Out
13.Description: Set when the extension timer gaps out.

15.Name: Extension Timer Reduction Start
15.Description: Set when extension timer starts to reduce (the time before reduction).

16.Name: Extension Timer Minimum Achieved
16.Description: Set when the extension timer minimum is reached (after the time to reduce).

17.Name: Added Initial Complete
17.Description: Set when added initial is achieved.

18.Name: Next Phase Decision
18.Description: Set when the controller determines a phase will be next to begin green after the current active phase(s) end red clearance.

19.Name: TSP Early Forceoff
19.Description: Set when TSP early forceoff is applied to an active phase.

20.Name: Preemption Forceoff
20.Description: Set when the controller applies preemption forceoff to the active cycle.

21.Name: Pedestrian Begin Walk
21.Description: Set when walk indication becomes active.

22.Name: Pedestrian Begin Clearance
22.Description: Set when flashing don't walk indication becomes active.

23.Name: Pedestrian Begin Steady Don't Walk
23.Description: Set when don't walk indication becomes steady (non flashing) from either termination of ped clearance, or after a dark interval.

24.Name: Pedestrian Dark
24.Description: Set when the pedestrian outputs are set off.

25.Name: Extended Pedestrian Change Interval
25.Description: Set when extended pedestrian change interval is requested.

31.Name: Barrier Termination
31.Description: Set when all active phases become inactive in the ring and cross barrier phases are next to be served.

33.Name: FYA - End Permissive
33.Description: Set when FYA becomes inactive through either clearance of the permissive movement or transition into a protected movement.

41.Name: Phase Hold Active
41.Description: Set when phase hold is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or external logic.

42.Name: Phase Hold Released
42.Description: Set when phase hold is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or external logic.

43.Name: Phase Call Registered
43.Description: Call to service on a phase is registered by vehicular demand.

44.Name: Phase Call Dropped
44.Description: Call to service on a phase is cleared by either service of the phase or removal of call.

45.Name: Pedestrian Call Registered
45.Description: Call to service on a phase is registered by pedestrian demand.

46.Name: Phase Omit On
46.Description: Set when phase omit is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources.

47.Name: Phase Omit Off
47.Description: Set when phase omit is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources.

48.Name: Pedestrian Omit On
48.Description: Set when ped omit is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources.

49.Name: Pedestrian Omit Off
49.Description: Set when ped omit is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources.

50.Name: MAX 1 In-Effect
50.Description: Set when maximum green (MAX 1) interval is in-effect for the active phase.

51.Name: MAX 2 In-Effect
51.Description: Set when maximum green (MAX 2) interval is in-effect for the active phase.

52.Name: Dynamic MAX In-Effect
52.Description: Set when dynamic max interval is in-effect for the active phase. Populated upon termination if MAX green (MAX 1 or MAX 2) interval

53.Name: Dynamic MAX Step Up
53.Description: Set when dynamic max interval steps up for the active phase (initially after two consecutive phase max out events).

54.Name: Dynamic MAX Step Down
54.Description: Set when dynamic max begins step down for the actuve phase (initially after two consecutive phase gap out events).

55.Name: Phase Advance Warning Sign On
55.Description: Set when advance warning sign is on.

56.Name: Phase Advance Warning Sign Off
56.Description: Set when advance warning sign is off.

61.Name: Overlap Begin Green
61.Description: Set when overlap becomes green. Do not set repeatedly when overlap is flashing green.

62.Name: Overlap Begin Trailing Green (Extension)
62.Description: Set when overlap is green and extension timers begin timing.

63.Name: Overlap Begin Yellow
63.Description: Set when overlap is in a yellow clearance state.

64.Name: Overlap Begin Red Clearance
64.Description: Set when overlap begins timing red clearance intervals.

65.Name: Overlap Off (Inactive with red indication)
65.Description: Set when overlap has completed all timing, allowing any conflicting phase next to begin service.

66.Name: Overlap Dark
66.Description: Set when overlap head is set dark (no active outputs).

67.Name: Pedestrian Overlap Begin Walk
67.Description: Set when walk indication becomes active.

68.Name: Pedestrian Overlap Begin Clearance
68.Description: Set when flashing don't walk indication becomes active.

69.Name: Pedestrian Overlap Begin Steady Don't Walk
69.Description: Set when don't walk indication becomes steady (non flashing) from either termination of ped clearance, or after a dark interval.

70.Name: Pedestrian Overlap Dark
70.Description: Set when the pedestrian outputs are set off.

71.Name: Overlap Advance Warning Sign On
71.Description: Set when advance warning sign becomes active.

72.Name: Overlap Advance Warning Sign Off
72.Description: Set when advance warning sign becomes inactive.

81.Name: Vehicle Detector Off
81.Description: Vehicle detector has turned off. Detector on and off events are triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.

82.Name: Vehicle Detector On
82.Description: Vehicle detector has turned on. Detector on and off events are triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.

83.Name: Vehicle Detector Restored
83.Description: Detector restored to non-failed state by either manual restoration or re-enabling via continued diagnostics.

84.Name: Vehicle Detector Fault- Other
84.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

85.Name: Vehicle Detector Fault- Watchdog
85.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

86.Name: Vehicle Detector Fault- Open Loop
86.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

87.Name: Vehicle Detector Fault- Shorted Loop
87.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

88.Name: Vehicle Detector Fault- Excessive Change
88.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

89.Name: Ped Detector Off
89.Description: Ped detector turned off. Detector events are triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.

90.Name: Ped Detector On
90.Description: Ped detector turned on. Detector events are triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.

91.Name: Ped Detector Failed
91.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

92.Name: Ped Detector Restored
92.Description: Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics.

93.Name: TSP Detector Off
93.Description: Set when TSP detector becomes inactive. TSP detector event occurs post any detector delay/extension.

94.Name: TSP Detector On
94.Description: Set when TSP detector is active. TSP detector event occurs post any detector delay/extension.

101.Name: Preempt Advance Warning Input
101.Description: Set when preemption advance warning input is activated.

102.Name: Preempt (Call) Input On
102.Description: Set when preemption input is activated.

103.Name: Preempt Gate Down Input Received
103.Description: Set when gate down input is received by the controller.

104.Name: Preempt (Call) Input Off
104.Description: Set when preemption input is de-activated.

105.Name: Preempt Entry Started
105.Description: Set when preemption delay expires and controller begins transition timing (forceoff) to serve preemption.

106.Name: Preemption Begin Track Clearance
106.Description: Set when track clearance phases are green and track clearance timing begins.

107.Name: Preemption Begin Dwell Service
107.Description: Set when preemption dwell or limited service begins or minimum dwell timer is reset due to call drop and reapplication.

108.Name: Preemption Link Active On
108.Description: Set when linked preemptor input is applied from active preemptor.

109.Name: Preemption Link Active Off
109.Description: Set when linked preemptor input is dropped from active preemptor.

110.Name: Preemption Max Presence Exceeded
110.Description: Set when preemption max presence timer is exceeded and preemption input is released from service.

111.Name: Preemption Begin Exit Interval
111.Description: Set when preemption exit interval phases are green and exit timing begins.

112.Name: TSP Check In
112.Description: Set when request for priority is received.

113.Name: TSP Adjustment to Early Green
113.Description: Set when controller is adjusting active cycle to accommodate early service to TSP phases.

114.Name: TSP Adjustment to Extend Green
114.Description: Set when controller is adjusting active cycle to accommodate extended service to TSP phases.

115.Name: TSP Check Out
115.Description: Set when the arrival time for the TSP event reaches zero.

116.Name: Preemption Forceoff
116.Description: Set when preemption applies forceoffs to any phase in the active cycle.

117.Name: TSP Early Forceoff
117.Description: Set when TSP early forceoff is applied to the active cycle.
